>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "bWwqM", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "oSTKY", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "zQtJ5", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>7</mn></mfrac></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/jee_main/images/ci/image10-b66191ba-b9cb-47c3-af38-d1c57da92dc1.jpg\" style=\"height: 119px; width: 200px;\" /></p><p>Let's say the bead loses contact with the ring at point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>, then&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&nbsp;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>\u00b0</mo><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>Applying the conservation of mechanical energy principle between <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> &amp; <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>R</mi><mfenced s